    One of the concepts that revolutionized the way we looked at costing was "customer lifecycle costing". This means anticipating all customer related costs at the initial stage before quoting a price to a customer. For instance, the number of hours spent on support throughout the lifecycle of a customer don't get accounted for as much as it should. When we account for the revenue generated vs. costs incurred throughout, ultimately the highest revenue generating customers can end up being the least profitable.

    Question - Is anyone in my network using customer lifecycle costing actively for contract costing?     hashtag #costing hashtag #accounting hashtag #cybersecurity
